<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🌉 M000 Week 3 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Bridge Building · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the steps. Circle your answer.</p>
<pre><code>repeat 3 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>How many blocks does the agent place? Circle one:</strong> 1 · 3 · 6</p>
<p><strong>What does it look like? Circle one:</strong> a line · a tower · a square</p>
<pre><code>repeat 5 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The gap is 5 blocks wide. Does the bridge reach the other side? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>How do you know? Circle one:</strong> it places 5 blocks for 5 spaces · it places only 3 blocks · it places nothing</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Clean steps first, then a broken version. Circle the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — The agent should build a bridge <strong>4 blocks long</strong>.</p>
<pre><code># clean
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
repeat 3 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Circle one:</strong> only 3 blocks, not 4 · one block too many · a wrong turn</p>
<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — The blocks should land in a line, next to each other.</p>
<pre><code># clean
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move up by 1
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Circle one:</strong> it moves up, not forward · a block is missing · wrong number</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>The agent should build a bridge <strong>6 blocks long</strong> using a loop. One part is missing.</p>
<pre><code>repeat ____ times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which number is missing? Circle one:</strong> 3 · 6 · 10</p>
<hr />
<h2>4 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Now switch to your homework world. Build a <strong>bridge across the river</strong> using a loop. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
